# Week 01 - AWS Internship Onboarding & Cloud Fundamentals

## 📌 Overview

The first week of AWS Workforce Bootcamp - First Cloud AI Journey focused on
understanding cloud computing fundamentals, AWS ecosystem, and preparing the
learning environment.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

- Understand basic concepts of Cloud Computing.
- Get familiar with AWS ecosystem.
- Setup AWS learning environment.
- Learn AWS core service categories.

---

# 📚 Learning Activities

## 1. Internship Onboarding

Topics covered:

- AWS company culture.
- Internship roadmap.
- Learning objectives.
- Working environment introduction.

---

## 2. Cloud Computing Fundamentals

Studied:

### Cloud Deployment Models

- Public Cloud
- Private Cloud
- Hybrid Cloud


### Cloud Service Models

| Model | Description |
|---|---|
| IaaS | Infrastructure as a Service |
| PaaS | Platform as a Service |
| SaaS | Software as a Service |

---

## 3. AWS Core Services Introduction

Explored:
AWS Cloud
│
├── Compute
│ └── Amazon EC2
│
├── Storage
│ └── Amazon S3
│
├── Database
│ └── Amazon RDS
│
└── Security
└── IAM

---

## 4. Environment Setup

Completed:

- AWS Account setup
- AWS Management Console exploration
- Development tools installation

---

# 🧠 Knowledge Gained

After completing this week:

- Understand basic cloud concepts.
- Understand AWS service categories.
- Know how to navigate AWS Console.
- Understand the role of cloud computing in modern applications.

---

# 📝 Notes

Cloud computing allows organizations to build scalable,
secure and cost-efficient applications without managing physical infrastructure.

